'''Pervis Josué Estupiñán Tenorio''' ({{IPA|es|estupiˈɲan}}; born 21 January 1998) is an Ecuadorian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|left-back]] and [[Defender (association football)#Wing-back|left wing-back]] for {{Italian football updater|Milan}} club [[AC Milan]] and the [[Ecuador national football team|Ecuador national team]].

==Club career==
===Early career===
[[File:Pervis Estupiñán 2015.jpg|thumb|upright|Estupiñán playing for [[L.D.U. Quito|LDU Quito]] in 2015]]

Born in [[Esmeraldas, Ecuador|Esmeraldas]], Estupiñán joined [[L.D.U. Quito|LDU Quito]]'s youth setup in 2011, aged 13. He was promoted to the first team ahead of the [[2015 Campeonato Ecuatoriano de Fútbol Serie A|2015 season]], and made his professional debut on 1 February of that year by starting in a 1–0 home win against [[C.D. El Nacional|El Nacional]].

=== Watford and following loans ===
An undisputed starter for the club, Estupiñán was sold to [[Premier League]] club [[Watford F.C.|Watford]] on 29 July 2016,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wdsport.co.uk/2016/07/watford-snare-trio-of-exciting-young-talent/|title=Watford snare trio of exciting young talent|publisher=WD Sport|date=29 July 2016|accessdate=18 March 2017}}</ref> being immediately loaned to [[Granada CF]] and assigned to the latter's [[Granada CF B|B-team]] in [[Segunda División B]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.granadacfweb.com/2016/07/29/pervis-estupinan-fichara-por-el-filial-rojiblanco/|title=Pervis Estupiñán fichará por el filial rojiblanco|trans-title=Pervis Estupiñán will sign for the reserve team ''rojiblanco''|publisher=Granada CF Web|language=es|date=29 July 2016|accessdate=18 March 2017}}</ref>

Estupiñán made his [[La Liga]] debut on 5 April 2017, starting in a 0–0 away draw against [[Deportivo de La Coruña]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.marca.com/eventos/marcador/futbol/2016_17/la-liga/jornada_30/dep_gda/|title=Ochoa no firma la rendición|trans-title=Ochoa does not sign the surrender|work=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]]|language=es|date=5 April 2017|accessdate=9 August 2017}}</ref> On 17 July, he was loaned to [[Segunda División]] side [[UD Almería]] for one year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.udalmeriasad.com/noticia/el-almeria-logra-del-watford-ingles-la-cesion-del-ecuatoriano-pervis-estupinan|title=El Almería logra del Watford inglés la cesión del ecuatoriano Pervis Estupiñán|trans-title=Almería get from English Watford the loan of Ecuadorian Pervis Estupiñán|publisher=UD Almería|language=es|date=17 July 2017|accessdate=18 July 2017}}</ref>

On 9 August 2018, Estupiñán agreed to a one-year loan deal with [[RCD Mallorca]] in the second division.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rcdmallorca.es/contenidos/noticias/noticia/pervis-estupinan-ficha-por-el-rcd-mallorca|title=Pervis Estupiñán ficha por el RCD Mallorca|trans-title=Pervis Estupiñán signs for RCD Mallorca|publisher=RCD Mallorca|language=es|date=9 August 2018|access-date=12 August 2018}}</ref> The following 3 July, after [[2018–19 Segunda División|achieving promotion]], he signed a two-year loan deal with [[CA Osasuna]], also freshly promoted.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.osasuna.es/noticia/_/13096/03-07-2019-osasuna-se-refuerza-con-pervis-estupinan.html|title=Osasuna se refuerza con Pervis Estupiñán|trans-title=Osasuna bolster with Pervis Estupiñán|publisher=CA Osasuna|language=es|date=3 July 2019|accessdate=4 July 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190703102724/https://www.osasuna.es/noticia/_/13096/03-07-2019-osasuna-se-refuerza-con-pervis-estupinan.html|archive-date=3 July 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref>

=== Villarreal ===

On 16 September 2020, Estupiñán signed a seven-year contract with Spanish side [[Villarreal CF|Villarreal]] for an initial fee of £14.9&nbsp;million.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.villarrealcf.es/noticias/todas-las-noticias/item/28508-bienvenido-estupinan|title=¡BIENVENIDO, ESTUPIÑÁN!|date=16 September 2020|accessdate=16 September 2020|publisher=Villarreal CF|language=Spanish}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Official: Estupiñán Joins Villarreal |url=https://www.watfordfc.com/news/official-estupinan-joins-villarreal |access-date=2026-04-25 |website=www.watfordfc.com}}</ref>

During his spell at the Valencian club, Estupiñán was a member of the squad that won the [[2020–21 UEFA Europa League]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/articles/clder77q96ko|title=Estupinan wants to 'leave mark' on Brighton|date=17 August 2022|access-date=26 November 2023|publisher=BBC}}</ref> and reached the semi-finals of the [[2021–22 UEFA Champions League]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=Naylor |first=Andy |date=2022-08-16 |title=Brighton close in on Pervis Estupinan to replace Marc Cucurella |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/3513415/2022/08/16/brighton-transfer-pervis-estupinan/ |access-date=2026-04-25 |work=The New York Times |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref>

=== Brighton and Hove Albion ===
On 16 August 2022, Estupiñán signed a five-year contract with [[Premier League]] side [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]] for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Hanson |first=Charlie |date=16 August 2022 |title=Pervis Estupinan joins from Villarreal |url=https://www.brightonandhovealbion.com/news/2746649/pervis-estupinan-joins-from-villarreal |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220816213755/https://www.brightonandhovealbion.com/news/2746649/pervis-estupinan-joins-from-villarreal |archive-date=16 August 2022 |access-date=2026-04-24 |website=www.brightonandhovealbion.com}}</ref> He made his debut four days later, coming on and replacing [[Adam Lallana]] in the 63rd minute in the 2–0 away win over [[West Ham United]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=Mann |first=Mantej |date=2022-08-19 |title=West Ham 0-2 Brighton & Hove Albion: David Moyes 'concerned' by toothless start |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/62537746 |access-date=2026-04-25 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> Estupiñán made his first start for the "Seagulls" on 27 August, helping Brighton to another win and clean sheet in the 1–0 home victory over [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=Howarth |first=Matthew |date=2022-08-26 |title=Brighton & Hove Albion 1-0 Leeds United: Pascal Gross strikes as Seagulls set club record |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/62614441 |access-date=2026-04-25 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> Estupiñán assisted [[2022 FIFA World Cup|returning World Cup champion]] [[Alexis Mac Allister]]'s flick-in in the 5–1 away victory over [[EFL Championship]] side [[Middlesbrough F.C.|Middlesbrough]] in the [[2022–23 FA Cup#third round|FA Cup third round]] on 7 January 2023.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Emerson |first=Palmieri |date=2023-04-25 |title=OKFUN |url=https://okfun-uytin.com/ |access-date=2026-04-25 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Five-star Albion cruise into the fourth round |url=https://www.brightonandhovealbion.com/news/3012703/five-star-albion-cruise-into-the-fourth-round |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230107215557/https://www.brightonandhovealbion.com/news/3012703/five-star-albion-cruise-into-the-fourth-round |archive-date=7 January 2023 |access-date=2026-04-24 |website=Brighton & Hove Albion}}</ref> Two weeks later, on his 25th birthday, he made a brace of assists, setting up both [[Kaoru Mitoma]]'s opening goal and [[Evan Ferguson]]'s late equaliser in the 2–2 away draw at [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]] in the league.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Talbot |first=Bruce |date=21 January 2023 |title=It's Fergie time as Evan's late leveller lifts Albion |url=https://www.brightonandhovealbion.com/news/3031868/its-fergie-time-as-evans-late-leveller-lifts-albion |archive-url=http://web.archive.org/web/20241005070335/https://www.brightonandhovealbion.com/news/3031868/its-fergie-time-as-evans-late-leveller-lifts-albion |archive-date=2024-10-05 |access-date=2026-04-25 |website=Brighton & Hove Albion}}</ref>

On 29 January, Estupiñán recorded his fourth assist of the season in a 2–1 victory over [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]], helping Brighton to advance to the fifth round of the [[2022–23 FA Cup|FA Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=It's magic from Mitoma as Albion beat Liverpool again |url=https://www.brightonandhovealbion.com/news/3040813/its-magic-from-mitoma-as-albion-beat-liverpool-again |access-date=2026-04-24 |website=Brighton & Hove Albion}}</ref> Two games later on 11 February, he added a further assist to his tally a 1–1 away draw against Crystal Palace. Early on in the game he had a goal wrongly ruled out by [[John Brooks (referee)|John Brooks]] of [[video assistant referee|VAR]] after the official drew the offside lines against the wrong player. Brooks was later dropped for his next two matches.<ref>{{Cite news |date=2023-02-10 |title=Crystal Palace 1-1 Brighton & Hove Albion: Seagulls held to frustrating draw |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/64520926 |access-date=2026-04-25 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-02-13 |title=Decision made as VAR official punished after Brighton blunder at Crystal Palace |url=https://www.sussexexpress.co.uk/sport/football/brighton-and-hove-albion/decision-made-as-var-official-punished-after-brighton-blunder-at-crystal-palace-including-liverpool-v-everton-and-arsenal-v-man-city-suspension-4024692 |access-date=2026-04-25 |website=SussexWorld |language=en}}</ref> Estupiñán scored his first goal for the Albion on 14 May, hitting in stoppage time, scoring the third in the 3–0 away win at [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]], while assisting [[Julio Enciso (footballer, born 2004)|Julio Enciso]]'s opener.<ref>{{Cite web |title=It's three and easy as magnificent Albion move up to sixth |url=https://www.brightonandhovealbion.com/news/3345249/its-three-and-easy-as-magnificent-albion-move-up-to-sixth |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230514180522/https://www.brightonandhovealbion.com/news/3345249/its-three-and-easy-as-magnificent-albion-move-up-to-sixth |archive-date=14 May 2023 |access-date=2026-04-24 |website=Brighton & Hove Albion}}</ref>

After setting up Mitoma's opener, Estupiñán scored his second Brighton goal in their second match of the [[2023–24 Brighton & Hove Albion F.C. season|2023–24 season]] on 19 August, in the 4–1 victory away at [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.brightonandhovealbion.com/news/3640283/albion-march-to-top-of-the-table|title=Albion March to top of the table|publisher=Brighton & Hove Albion|date=19 August 2023|access-date=19 August 2023|archive-date=19 August 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230819164039/https://www.brightonandhovealbion.com/news/3640283/albion-march-to-top-of-the-table|url-status=dead}}</ref>

On 28 December, after months out due to injury, Estupiñán scored a long-range goal after coming on as a substitute at halftime in a 4–2 win against [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=Hytner |first=David |date=2023-12-28 |title=Tottenham battered despite late rally after Estupiñán provides Brighton fizz |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/dec/28/brighton-tottenham-premier-league-match-report |access-date=2026-04-25 |work=The Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref>

=== AC Milan ===

On 24 July 2025, Estupiñán signed a five-year contract with Italian [[Serie A]] side [[AC Milan]] for an undisclosed fee, reported to be at least £17 million. This signing made him the first Ecuadorian in the club's history.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.acmilan.com/en/news/articles/media/2025-07-24/official-statement-pervis-estupinan|title=Official Statement: Pervis Estupiñán|date=24 July 2025|access-date=24 July 2025|website=acmilan.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/c93937pkq7qo|title=AC Milan sign Brighton defender Estupinan for £17m|date=24 July 2025|access-date=24 July 2025|website=BBC Sport|last=Fletcher |first=Alex}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last= |first= |title=Brighton star Estupinan seals move to AC Milan |url=https://www.beinsports.com/en-au/football/serie-a/articles-video/brighton-star-estupinan-seals-move-to-ac-milan-2025-07-24 |access-date=2026-04-25 |website=beIN SPORTS |language=en-au}}</ref>

On 8 March 2026, he scored his first goal with the club during a 1–0 home win Serie A match against [[Inter Milan]], on the ''[[Derby della Madonnina]]''.<ref>{{Cite web |date=8 March 2026 |title=Pervis Estupiñán marcó su primer gol con Milan en el Derby ante Inter por Serie A |url=https://espndeportes.espn.com/futbol/italia/nota/_/id/16408409/video-golazo-de-pervis-estupinan-para-milan-ante-inter |access-date=8 March 2026 |language=Spanish |website=[[ESPN Deportes]]|trans-title=Pervis Estupiñán scored his first goal for Milan in the Derby against Inter in Serie A}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=8 March 2026 |title=Pervis Estupiñán marca gol histórico y da victoria al AC Milan ante Inter |url=https://www.elcomercio.com/deportes/futbol/pervis-estupinan-gol-historico-milan-inter/ |access-date=8 March 2026 |language=Spanish |website=[[El Comercio (Ecuador)|El Comercio]]|trans-title=Pervis Estupiñán scores a historic goal and gives AC Milan the victory against Inter}}</ref>

==International career==
Estupiñán made his debut for the [[Ecuador national football team|Ecuador national team]] on 13 October 2019 in a friendly against Argentina that ended in a 6–1 loss.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[ESPN]]|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/lineups?gameId=557810|title=Ecuador v Argentina game report|date=13 October 2019}}</ref>

Estupiñán played for Ecuador at the [[2019 Copa América]] and was named in the Team of the Tournament<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.france24.com/en/live-news/20220816-brighton-sign-ecuador-s-estupinan-from-villarreal|title= Brighton sign Ecuador's Estupinan from Villarreal|date=17 August 2022|access-date=26 November 2023|publisher=France 24}}</ref> as ''La Tri'' reached the quarter-finals.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://villarrealcf.es/en/estupinan-through-to-the-copa-america-quarter-finals/|title=Estupiñán through to the Copa América quarter-finals|date=28 June 2023|access-date=26 November 2023|publisher=Villarreal CF}}</ref>

On 14 November, Estupiñán was named in Ecuador's 26-man squad for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] alongside Brighton teammates [[Jeremy Sarmiento]] and [[Moisés Caicedo]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://espndeportes.espn.com/futbol/mundial/nota/_/id/11228629/ecuador-lista-convocados-qatar-2022-mundial-copa-mundo |title=Ecuador, el último en entregar la lista de los 26 jugadores convocados para la Copa del Mundo de Qatar 2022 |trans-title=Ecuador, the last to deliver the list of the 26 players summoned for the Qatar World Cup 2022 |work=[[ESPN Deportes]] |date=14 November 2022 |access-date=15 November 2022 |language=es}}</ref>

